news.title: Raipur civic body asks builders to construct 50 rainwater harvesting pits each
news.para: The RMC has set a target of constructing 50,000 rainwater harvesting pits including 20,000 pits in the current monsoon season. A single pit can conserve 2 lakh litres of rainwater.

news.title: Rent dues mount, stores at Gurugram's rapid rail station sealed
news.para: A total of 1,956 sq ft, covering seven shops, is registered under owner, Sunil Miglani, said sub-divisional engineer Naresh Kumar Rana.

news.title: Over 23,800 people in Delhi received ownership rights of properties under PM-UDAY: Govt
news.para: ​In a written reply to a question, Minister of State for Housing and Urban Affairs Tokhan Sahu said the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) has received 1,22,729 applications for ownership rights under the PM-UDAY.

news.title: WeWork India adds over 1.4 lakh sq ft with new centers in Bengaluru and Noida
news.para: WeWork 37 Cunningham is a four-story workspace with over 1,000 desks across over 60,000 sq ft while WeWork Galaxy Business Park has over 1,400 desks across 79,000 sq ft.

news.title: Synq.work plans to invest Rs 60 crore to add six lakh sq ft in Bengaluru, Pune & Hyderabad
news.para: Synq.Work plans to expand the current seating capacity from 3,200 to 12,000 by adding an additional 8800 seats by December 2025

news.title: Home First Finance Company's net profit up 27% at Rs 88 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Its assets under management grew 35% on year to Rs. 10,478 crores, while loan disbursement grew 30% on year to Rs. 1,163 crores. About 86% of its portfolio comprises housing loans with average ticket size of Rs 11.6 lakh.

news.title: Noida builders who signed up for reschedulement policy to be screened for second waiver
news.para: Of the 27 of 57 builders in Noida who had agreed to the terms, about 10-11 are eligible for this additional relief – applicable for the period from Aug 14, 2013 to Aug 19, 2015.

news.title: NCLT approves Alchemist Infra Realty's acquisition by Vantage Point Asset Management
news.para: The company’s resolution professional had received a claim of Rs 1,293 crore and the successful bidder is paying about Rs 470 crore to acquire the company through the insolvency resolution process.

news.title: The Ramco Cements' net profit down 51% to Rs 36.57 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: ​The company posted a net profit of Rs 74.36 crore during the April-June quarter of the previous fiscal, The Ramco Cements said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Singapore central bank proposes simplified leverage provisions for REITs
news.para: All Singapore REITs will be subject to a minimum interest coverage ratio (ICR) threshold of 1.5 times and an aggregate leverage limit of 50%, under the proposal brought forth by the Monetary Authority of Singapore.

news.title: Blackstone's battered mortgage fund slumps as empty offices intensify pressure
news.para: It is the latest sign of mounting woes in commercial real estate. Analysts are predicting more weakness for lenders and owners in the sector as American workers maintain their pandemic-era remote work habits.

news.title: PNB Housing's net profit up 25% to Rs 433 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Total income during the quarter rose to Rs 1,832 crore from Rs 1,708 crore in the same quarter of the previous fiscal, PNB Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Embassy REIT's net operating income up 3% to Rs 757.5 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: The board of directors of Embassy Office Parks Management Services Pvt Ltd, Manager to Embassy REIT, at its board meeting, declared a distribution of Rs 531 crore or Rs 5.60 per unit for the first quarter of 2024-25.

news.title: Apco Infratech buys 9,527 sq ft apartment in Pali Hill from Ashar Group for Rs 172 crore
news.para: This transaction was achieved at the rate of Rs 1.81 lakh per sq ft and the buyer has paid a stamp duty of Rs 9.30 crore.

news.title: NPKL allottees slam Bengaluru development body's decision to collect road-cutting fee
news.para: The Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout Open Forum wrote a letter to the Chief Minister on May 14, 2024, directing the BDA not to collect Rs 31,000 from the site owners.

news.title: The land ownership conundrum in village of South Delhi
news.para: Lal Dora was used in the past to demarcate the jurisdiction of a village on land where the population resided. When the population increased and villagers got a plot for a house against their scattered agricultural land holdings under the ‘chakbandi’ scheme, the concept of extended Lal Dora was introduced.

news.title: Housing board buildings unsafe, need urgent help: Goa legislators
news.para: Speaking during a calling attention motion in the assembly, they said these buildings are in a very fragile state, with families still residing in them. The MLAs called on govt to take action before any untoward incident occurs.

news.title: Goa's cabinet approve bill to take over land with no owners
news.para: The proposal also seeks to introduce a comprehensive legislative framework to govern the manegement of specific types of property that become vested in state govt.
